#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/security-properties.md:1
msgid "Security Properties"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/security-properties.md:3
msgid "Validate at boundaries, trust internally (`validate-at-boundaries`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/security-properties.md:5
msgid ""
"Designate certain interfaces as validation boundaries. In Asterinas, syscall "
"entry points are the primary boundary: all user-supplied data (pointers, "
"file descriptors, sizes, flags, strings) must be validated at the syscall "
"boundary. Once validated, internal kernel functions may trust these values "
"without re-validation."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/security-properties.md:14
msgid ""
